<html><head></head><body dir=3D"auto" style=3D"overflow-wrap: =
break-word; -webkit-nbsp-mode: space; line-break: =
after-white-space;"><div><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;">Good afternoon David and Chris,</p><p dir=3D"auto" =
style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Thank you for your follow-up email, =
David, and for clarifying the misunderstanding from our call. I =
appreciate your offer to meet and your flexibility with Tuesday or =
Wednesday, Wednesday could work, how about 2pm.</p><p dir=3D"auto" =
style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Also not to waste resources and time, I =
would like to re-iterate the key priorities</p><p dir=3D"auto" =
style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;"><ul class=3D"MailOutline"><li>we must =
address Health &amp; Safety (H&amp;S) risk identification and mitigation =
before any work starts - and</li><li>the work should focus on enabling =
to assess the damages-independently and agree a plan for =
remediation</li></ul></p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;"><br></p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">As =
per what I have been told by the Fire-ifghters there have been  =
substantial fire damage and significant smoke was exiting the =
roof=E2=80=94initially thought to originate there by Devonport Flagstaff =
- and gone through the house structure to be able to exit from the roof. =
Yet, the whole structure  - impacted by smoke, heat air fire - and  the =
roof and the gas unit beneath it remain uninspected, alongside concerns =
about asbestos and structural integrity. A master electrician has also =
deemed the property uninhabitable due to electrical hazards, which =
heightens my worry about the proposed scope.</p><p dir=3D"auto" =
style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">I=E2=80=99m particularly concerned =
about the asbestos plan. The scope mentions removing less than 10m=C2=B2, =
but the deck=E2=80=99s fire-damaged section connects to the main area, =
suggesting potential wider involvement.</p><p dir=3D"auto" =
style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;"> I=E2=80=99ve raised this with Chris, =
requesting a full inspection, and I=E2=80=99d like that addressed before =
any removal begins.&nbsp;</p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;">More broadly, I=E2=80=99m uneasy about sequencing=E2=80=94a =
lot of the cleaning work seems like repair work rather than assessment. =
I=E2=80=99d prefer we limit initial work to actions that enable damage =
assessment, like securing the site or removing debris for inspection, =
allowing me to seek an independent view on the full extent of damage. =
This seems fair to ensure safety and accuracy, doesn=E2=80=99t it?</p><p =
dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">Could we please align on =
this H&amp;S-first, assessment-only approach? I=E2=80=99d be grateful if =
you could confirm Wednesday or suggest other times to discuss this =
onsite.&nbsp;</p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: pre-wrap;">While  =
I=E2=80=99m meeting a lawyer tomorrow morning and will seek further =
guidance, I=E2=80=99m keen to collaborate with you both for a safe, fair =
 and thorough process.</p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;">Thanks so much for your understanding=E2=80=94I look forward =
to your response.</p><p dir=3D"auto" style=3D"white-space: =
pre-wrap;">Kind regards,<br>
Raffaella del Prete</p></div><div><br></div>On 30 Jun 2025, at =
11:25=E2=80=AFAM, David Tallot &lt;david@assetrestore.co.nz&gt; =
